Death has visited one of the most respected families in Nigeria and it has taken away their patriarch, billionaire Bolu Akin-Olugbade. During his lifetime, the socialite who reportedly died due to COVID-19 complications made news headlines for his love for the Rolls Royce. He recently acquired a brand new Rolls Royce automobile called The Cullinan. It was his 63rd birthday gift to himself and the number plate is BOLU 10. At a time, it was gathered that he had 10 Rolls Royce Limousines in his exotic garage and has been driving the automobiles since 1984.